I came to Blue Door with low expectations, with lots of Mediterranean cuisine under my belt (or in my belly you could say) and was really impressed.  The server was quick to accommodate us, and make us a table on the sidewalk so we didn’t have to wait. We ordered the whole lot, and had such a wide variety of items. Portions are great, prices are good, and most importantly, the food was great. Nothing specific I would recommend, because it’s all good.  I was even impressed with the octopus, and it’s a hard dish to pull off. Not perfect, but not bad either.  Service was at times slow, so we saw the server handling the register and other duties, but totally understandable given the current circumstances.  We really enjoyed our time here. Another reviewer complained about the price of lamb chops....lamb chops are bloody expensive to buy in the first place for restaurants!

This is more so a suggestion than a critique. I did enjoy the ambiance at this restaurant. The space is beautiful and even in current circumstances, Blue Door Souvlakia has managed to create a great atmosphere. The menu is great, the drinks are great. Even the take out boxes and bags are beautiful. That being said, with such great attention to detail you can imagine my surprise when I paid $28 for 3 lamb chops and a less than generous portion of lentil rice. What’s even more astonishing is that the rice outshined the lamb. Looking around at other diners that opted for platters or even smaller dishes like skewers seemed more satisfying. I don’t know what the restaurant has endured, nor do I know it’s practices or it’s vendors pricing. But I don’t think I need to elaborate on the variety of entrees available in competing restaurants for about the same price with at LEAST two sides available. Please consider adding sauce, pita or salad to that dish at minimum. Especially if there are lower priced items on your menu available with greater portions. Especially if the lamb itself is not going to be show stopping , as I was told that lamb is a specialty at the restaurant only available on weekends. All the best!

Food was tasty with good prices. Service were ok, server was not very attentive. On Friday I went there with the children and we ate a very good dinner. The bill was at around $ 80. With tip I paid $ 100. The waitress took my credit card and collected two different sums around of $ 90 and $ 190, none of it  was my bill for dinner. In total, the dinner amounted $ 280. It was probably one of my most expensive dinners. I went to the restaurant on Sunday but there was no boss. The waitress took my phone number and said that the boss would call me back the same day  or the next morning. She didn’t  call me back, after two days I received a phone call. Some woman said  that there were a lot of people in the restaurant and the waitress was make the mistake.  She didn’t even apologize to me. At the end she taken $ 100 from my  account and She didn’t even ask me if I still want to give a tip for the waitress, although then I had serious doubts :( I am honestly disappointed with the service and lack of respect for the client.
